However, the PC/Console is recommended for the controls are clunky at worst and are slow.

Excellent game better than the psx version. The graphics are great and things have been polished up nicely for the Android port. I'm an Oddworld fan and am glad to see the nice graphical upgrades they've done for this port of an excellent game. My only issue is one I won't necessarily ding them for because, though powerful, I have an older phone. It's just that in certain levels the fps drops immensely to the point of frustration. Tweaking with the settings can help, but not all the way. By contrast, although there is a strange issue with tearing occasionally with Stranger's Wrath, it runs smoothly yet had graphics designed for the Xbox. I'd recommend playing this with a Bluetooth controller, as it was meant to be played, it works excellent and helps you react quicker, although, the touch controls are better than most. All and all, it's good to see the oddworld games getting some love and I hope beyond hope that we finally get the last 2 inhabitants and hopefully a final game that ties them all together. Also, here's hoping we see Abes exodus soon!

The game is great. It is a great game when played on other platforms. On my Xperia XZ Premium I have a gamebreaking problem. When playing the game it constantly begins to flicker making the game unplayable. This doesnt happen on my Xperia Z4 Tablet but that has a native 1440p resolution even still the game runs fairly slow on this device which still has decent specs.  I put it down to the XZ Premium's 4k display which only goes 2160p on certain apps (1080p on others). Never have I experienced so much lag and flickering on an android app though. Its mainly noticeable when interacting with the system ui in mid game such as reading notifications and especially when adjusting the volume.  I hope this issue gets addressed as the game is unplayable. Will rate with 5 stars if it does as the game itself is great, just that performance sucks on Android pretty badly. Alot of other users also experience this and it should be fixed.
replyContent: The XZ1 (premium or not) can run the game at 720p at best. Does lowering the resolution slider to the lowest or second lowest setting help?
